OL,3,CBoy, 15, died trying to save friend in
OL,4,Ctragic quarry accident
OL,6,FWhen Ms Saunders asked what in his
OL,7,Fview had happened, he said evidence
OL,8,Ffrom Mr Whitelock seemed to suggest
OL,9,Fthat one person was "slightly lower
OL,10,Fthan the other".
OL,12,FHe added: "From the description it
OL,13,Fwould have appeared to me that the
OL,14,Fteenage girl was on a slightly lower
OL,15,Fledge, she's slipped, she's gone
OL,16,Fdown... and Myron has gone over. A
OL,17,Fthought process is that the teenage
OL,18,Fgirl has slipped and Myron has gone to
OL,19,Ftry and help her - an automatic
OL,20,Freaction when someone trips in front
OL,21,Fof you."
